win31x (0.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.
  * Use categorized high-resolution artwork from the user-supplied Windows 98
    icon archive for the desktop, launcher, minimized clients, and title bars.
  * Make click-to-focus reliably raise clients, including applications with
    their own passive button grabs, and harden focus and transient lifecycle
    handling.
  * Correct desktop-entry escaping, working directories, deep discovery, and
    resize-increment handling; expand real-pointer and provenance tests.
  * Correct bordered-client geometry, window gravity, stack requests, root
    resizing, launcher resizing, and shift-free client withdrawal.
  * Install the supplied session icon through hicolor, enable full hardening,
    and run the Xvfb/XTEST suite during package and QEMU provisioning.
  * Add a desktop Control Panel using the supplied settings, network, display,
    and clock artwork. Configure NetworkManager Wi-Fi, persistent live color
    schemes, and xss-lock/xsecurelock idle locking without exposing passwords
    in process arguments or logs.
  * Extend the XTEST regression suite through the Control Panel and retain
    reliable click-to-focus/raise behavior when its internal window is open.
  * Show visible asterisk feedback for xsecurelock passwords on both idle and
    Lock Now paths, with child-environment regression coverage.
  * Reinstall rebuilt packages during repeat QEMU provisioning even when the
    package version is unchanged.
  * Fail fast when X11, libpng, or XTEST build dependencies are missing, keep
    mandatory linker and sanitizer flags under common make overrides, and add
    clean Debian CI coverage for those failure modes.
  * Add maximize/restore controls and left/right screen-edge snap for managed
    clients, Applications, and Control Panel, including EWMH maximize state.
  * Keep Applications and Control Panel mapped independently across focus
    changes and launches until explicitly closed with X or Alt+F4.
  * Add a Windows/Super+R Run dialog with direct, shell-free argument parsing
    and executable validation.
  * Use each desktop entry's real hicolor or pixmaps PNG/XPM icon in
    Applications, and use client-provided _NET_WM_ICON artwork in title bars
    and minimized desktop icons, retaining supplied Win98 artwork as fallback.
  * Add a focus-preserving right-click desktop menu for Lock, Log Out, Restart,
    and Shut Down. Invoke power actions through validated, direct systemctl
    argument vectors and cover every action without powering off test systems.
  * Require classic confirmation dialogs before Log Out, Restart, and Shut
    Down, with a safe default and lock-screen-aware modality; keep Lock
    immediate.
  * Use classic rubber-band outlines for title-bar moves and commit the real
    window geometry on button release, reducing repaint tearing under Xorg and
    QEMU while preserving left/right edge snap.
  * Add RandR 1.5 monitor discovery with an Xinerama fallback. Keep maximize,
    edge snap, desktop icons, internal windows, menus, Run and power dialogs
    on the appropriate monitor, and reflow them after display-layout changes.
  * Persist draggable desktop-icon positions, Applications, Control Panel and
    Run geometry, managed application geometry, colors, and the selected
    Control Panel section in private, versioned per-user configuration files;
    preserve future schemas and safely bound malformed coordinates.

 -- Win31 X maintainers <maintainers@win31x.invalid>  Sat, 18 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0800
